						<div class="postbody">I feel like the Nintendo I knew died a slow death starting with the N64.<br />Since the N64, games from Big N kept getting less and less challenging. The motion controls really put me off, especially for games like Donkey Kong Country Returns, because it's so imprecise. Platformers really require precision timing that motion controls don't offer.<br /><br />I was about ready to give up on newer games completely until I discovered Demon's Souls and Dark Souls and all the great indie games like Braid, VVVVVV, Cave Story, Super Meat Boy, etc<br /><br />I'm still hoping arcade style games make a comeback, I'm really sick of casual games.</div>

